For a positive integer \(m\), the set \(\left\{1,\cdots,m\right\}\) is abbreviated as \([m]\). The set of multi-indexes whose size is \(m\) or is at most \(m\) is referred by

\[I_{m} =\left\{\alpha=(\alpha_{1},\ldots,\alpha_{d})\in\mathbb{N}_{0}^{d} :|\alpha|=\sum_{i=1}^{d}\alpha_{i}=m\right\},\] (18) \[J_{m} =\left\{\alpha=(\alpha_{1},\ldots,\alpha_{d})\in\mathbb{N}_{0}^{d }:|\alpha|=\sum_{i=1}^{d}\alpha_{i}\leq m\right\}.\]

In this paper, we use two-layer MLPs. For given \(k\in\mathbb{N}\) and a partition \(0=\xi_{0}<\xi_{1}<\cdots<\xi_{L}<\xi_{L+1}=k\), we define \(\phi_{\ell}:\mathbb{R}^{d}\rightarrow\mathbb{R}^{|I_{\xi_{\ell}}|}\) of width \(m\) as

\[\phi_{\ell}\left(\bm{x};\bm{w}_{\ell},\bm{v}_{\ell}\right) =\frac{1}{\sqrt{m}}\sum_{r=1}^{m}\left(\bm{v}_{\ell}\right)_{r} \sigma\left(\left[\left(\bm{w}_{\ell}\right)_{r,1}\quad\left(\bm{w}_{\ell} \right)_{r,2}\quad\cdots\quad\left(\bm{w}_{\ell}\right)_{r,d}\right]\bm{x}+ \frac{1}{2}\left(\bm{w}_{\ell}\right)_{r,d+1}\right)\] (19) \[=\frac{1}{\sqrt{m}}\sum_{r=1}^{m}\left(\bm{v}_{\ell}\right)_{r} \sigma\left(\left(\bm{w}_{\ell}\right)_{r}^{\top}\bm{y}\right),\]

where weights in the first and second layer are

\[\left(\bm{w}_{\ell}\right)_{r} =\left[\left(\bm{w}_{\ell}\right)_{r,1}\quad\left(\bm{w}_{\ell} \right)_{r,2}\quad\cdots\quad\left(\bm{w}_{\ell}\right)_{r,d}\ \ \tfrac{1}{2}\left(\bm{w}_{\ell}\right)_{r,d+1}\right]^{\top}\in\mathbb{R}^{(d+ 1)},\] (20) \[\left(\bm{v}_{\ell}\right)_{r} =\left[\left(\bm{v}_{\ell}\right)_{r,1}\quad\left(\bm{v}_{\ell} \right)_{r,2}\quad\cdots\quad\left(\bm{v}_{\ell}\right)_{r,|I_{\xi_{\ell}}|} \right]^{\top}\in\mathbb{R}^{|I_{\xi_{\ell}}|},\] (21)

